\newlabel{tab:attribution}{{7}{15}{Causal-attribution efficiency from oracle interventions. Efficiency is defined as $\Delta $success divided by oracle activation rate for the corresponding task and regime. For hazard recovery, retrieval/materialization repair is substantially more effective per activation opportunity than controller repair; for goal-region, none of the isolated interventions improves end-to-end success despite high activation of retrieval/materialization repair}{table.7}{}}
